CAPE TOWN – "Help us or we won’t vote," fed-up landless Gugulethu residents in Cape Town told government on Friday. Human settlements minister Nomaindiya Mfeketo met with some of the 15,000 people living in backyards in and around the Cape Flats township. READ: Another land grab in Durban The group grew impatient with promises made, saying they have heard them time and time again. eNCA’s Pheladi Sethusa was there. Watch the full report above. eNCA